Earlier today, Chaz tweeted: 'Thanks for your concern about our separation. I'm doing fine, and we remain on good terms with nothing but respect and affection 4 eachother.'

Just last month singer Cher’s transgender son, was shown popping the question during his one-hour TV-show special Being Chaz, which aired on the Oprah Winfrey Network.

The programme was a follow-up to his Emmy-nominated documentary Becoming Chaz which focused on his transition from female to male.

Elia - who writing a book - supported the 42-year-old during his gender reassignment process and later said she found her partner 'more attractive' as a man.

She said that their intimate relationship as 'straight couple' improved 'for the good.'

